				</ukm:Metadata><Secondary><Schedules RestrictExtent="E+W+S" RestrictStartDate="2026-04-06"><Schedule DocumentURI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/uksi/2013/376/schedule/4" IdURI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2013/376/schedule/4" NumberOfProvisions="40" id="schedule-4" RestrictStartDate="2026-04-06"><Number>SCHEDULE 4</Number><TitleBlock><Title>Housing costs element for renters</Title></TitleBlock><ScheduleBody><Part DocumentURI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/uksi/2013/376/schedule/4/part/3" IdURI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2013/376/schedule/4/part/3" NumberOfProvisions="15" id="schedule-4-part-3" RestrictStartDate="2026-04-06"><Number><Strong>PART 3</Strong></Number><Title>General provisions about calculation of amount of housing costs element for renters</Title><Pblock DocumentURI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/uksi/2013/376/schedule/4/part/3/crossheading/housing-cost-contributions" IdURI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2013/376/schedule/4/part/3/crossheading/housing-cost-contributions" NumberOfProvisions="4" id="schedule-4-part-3-crossheading-housing-cost-contributions" RestrictStartDate="2026-04-06"><Title><Emphasis>Housing cost contributions</Emphasis></Title><P1group RestrictExtent="E+W+S" RestrictStartDate="2026-04-06"><Title>Amount of housing cost contributions</Title><P1 DocumentURI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/uksi/2013/376/schedule/4/paragraph/14" IdURI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2013/376/schedule/4/paragraph/14" id="schedule-4-paragraph-14"><Pnumber>14</Pnumber><P1para><P2 DocumentURI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/uksi/2013/376/schedule/4/paragraph/14/1" IdURI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2013/376/schedule/4/paragraph/14/1" id="schedule-4-paragraph-14-1"><Pnumber>1</Pnumber><P2para><Text>The amount of each housing cost contribution to be deducted under paragraph 13 is <Substitution ChangeId="key-c4f0ebc2863900e579139e70c3e15e1d-1775732433525" CommentaryRef="key-c4f0ebc2863900e579139e70c3e15e1d">£96.55</Substitution>.</Text></P2para></P2><P2 DocumentURI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/uksi/2013/376/schedule/4/paragraph/14/2" IdURI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2013/376/schedule/4/paragraph/14/2" id="schedule-4-paragraph-14-2"><Pnumber>2</Pnumber><P2para><Text>Deductions are not to be made until the amount has been determined which results from all other steps in the calculation required in relation to the renter under Parts 4 and 5 of this Schedule.</Text></P2para></P2><P2 DocumentURI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/uksi/2013/376/schedule/4/paragraph/14/3" IdURI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2013/376/schedule/4/paragraph/14/3" id="schedule-4-paragraph-14-3" RestrictStartDate="2017-04-10"><Pnumber>3</Pnumber><P2para><Text>Where the sum of all the housing cost contributions to be deducted in the renter's case exceeds the amount referred to in sub-paragraph (2)—</Text><P3 DocumentURI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/uksi/2013/376/schedule/4/paragraph/14/3/a" IdURI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2013/376/schedule/4/paragraph/14/3/a" id="schedule-4-paragraph-14-3-a" RestrictStartDate="2017-04-10"><Pnumber><CommentaryRef Ref="key-31a621c105ef07d885f403d100919cde"/>a</Pnumber><P3para><Text>the amount determined under this Schedule is to be reduced to nil; but</Text></P3para></P3><P3 DocumentURI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/uksi/2013/376/schedule/4/paragraph/14/3/b" IdURI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2013/376/schedule/4/paragraph/14/3/b" id="schedule-4-paragraph-14-3-b"><Pnumber>b</Pnumber><P3para><Text>no further reduction in respect of housing cost contributions is to be made from the renter's award.</Text></P3para></P3></P2para></P2></P1para></P1></P1group></Pblock></Part></ScheduleBody></Schedule></Schedules></Secondary><Commentaries><Commentary id="key-31a621c105ef07d885f403d100919cde" Type="C"><Para><Text>Sch. 4 para. 14(3)(a) sum maintained (coming into force in accordance with art. 1(2)(o) of the amending S.I.) by <Citation URI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2017/260" id="rnb8sic5-d3e43862a1310" Class="UnitedKingdomStatutoryInstrument" Year="2017" Number="260" Title="The Social Security Benefits Up-rating Order 2017">The Social Security Benefits Up-rating Order 2017 (S.I. 2017/260)</Citation>, <CitationSubRef CitationRef="rnb8sic5-d3e43862a1310" id="rnb8sic5-d3e43865a1310" URI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2017/260/article/1/2/o" SectionRef="article-1-2-o">arts. 1(2)(o)</CitationSubRef>, <CitationSubRef CitationRef="rnb8sic5-d3e43862a1310" id="rnb8sic5-d3e43868a1310" URI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2017/260/article/28/3/b" SectionRef="article-28-3-b" Operative="true">28(3)(b)</CitationSubRef></Text></Para></Commentary><Commentary id="key-c4f0ebc2863900e579139e70c3e15e1d" Type="F"><Para><Text>Sum in <CitationSubRef id="c5dof8ng6-00007" SectionRef="schedule-4-paragraph-14-1" URI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2013/376/schedule/4/paragraph/14/1">Sch. 4 para. 14(1)</CitationSubRef>  substituted (coming into force in accordance with art. 1(3)(n) of the amending S.I.) by <Citation URI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2026/148" id="c5dof8ng6-00008" Class="UnitedKingdomStatutoryInstrument" Year="2026" Number="148" Title="The Social Security Benefits Up-rating Order 2026">The Social Security Benefits Up-rating Order 2026 (S.I. 2026/148)</Citation>, <CitationSubRef CitationRef="c5dof8ng6-00008" id="c5dof8ng6-00009" SectionRef="article-1-3-n" URI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2026/148/article/1/3/n">arts. 1(3)(n)</CitationSubRef>, <CitationSubRef CitationRef="c5dof8ng6-00008" id="c5dof8ng6-00010" SectionRef="article-32-3" URI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2026/148/article/32/3" Operative="true">32(3)</CitationSubRef></Text></Para></Commentary></Commentaries></Legislation>